$ SQL Server: datatype sql_variant
@ sql_variant

An `sql_variant` allows to store values of different data types. The concept of `sql_variant` is the same as that of the → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/variant[VBA datatype `variant`].

sa:

  The → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/functions/sql_variant_property[`sql_variant_property`] function can be used to query an `sql_variant` value's base type and other properties.

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types
